## Limitations

The analysis is limited by the availability of sources and the potential bias in interpretations of Durkheim's theories. Additionally, the discussion is largely theoretical and may not fully account for the complexities of crime in contemporary society. The reliance on secondary sources, such as online forums and non-peer-reviewed articles, may also affect the depth and accuracy of the findings. Further empirical research is needed to substantiate the theoretical claims regarding the necessity of crime in society.